  "text": "Much like [CITATION_1] study in which individuals focusing on whitejerseyed players were less likely to notice an all-black gorilla, [CITATION_2] found that when individuals focused on a group of letters, 66% of participants noticed an unexpected letter \"E\" enter and exit the screen. When individuals were instead focused on a set of numbers, only 39% noticed the letter \"E\" enter their field of view. As [CITATION_3] explains, this is due to individuals tuning their attention to the features of the category they were tasked to observe, in essence forming a set of relevant features to look out for.",
